{"questionId": "555c176c-fa9a-40e0-b8a8-cb40b47c9ee3_14", "correctAnswer": "C", "section": "Math", "steps": [{"title": "Use vertex form with the given vertex", "content": "Since the graph has vertex at $(1, 4)$, use the vertex form $f(x) = a(x - 1)^2 + 4$, where $a$ is the coefficient we need to find.", "formula": "$$f(x) = a(x - h)^2 + k$$"}, {"title": "Find coefficient $a$ using point $(2, 27)$", "content": "Substitute the point $(2, 27)$ into the vertex form:<br/>$$27 = a(2 - 1)^2 + 4$$<br/>$$27 = a + 4$$<br/>$$a = 23$$<br/>Verify with point $(-1, 96)$: $f(-1) = 23(-1 - 1)^2 + 4 = 23(4) + 4 = 96$ ✓"}, {"title": "Calculate $f(-2) - f(0)$", "content": "With $f(x) = 23(x - 1)^2 + 4$, evaluate both values:<br/>$$f(-2) = 23(-2 - 1)^2 + 4 = 23(9) + 4 = 207 + 4 = 211$$<br/>$$f(0) = 23(0 - 1)^2 + 4 = 23(1) + 4 = 27$$<br/>$$f(-2) - f(0) = 211 - 27 = 184$$<br/>That matches choice C — <strong>C</strong> is correct."}]}